and I would love to hear

00:36:24.760 --> 00:36:26.760
what this recent LinkedIn post was too.

00:36:28.520 --> 00:36:31.399
So yeah, I had talked on LinkedIn

00:36:31.399 --> 00:36:34.120
about being a square peg in a round hole,

00:36:34.760 --> 00:36:37.399
being a statistician but not doing statistics,

00:36:37.399 --> 00:36:38.520
being a data scientist

00:36:38.520 --> 00:36:41.000
but not fitting machine learning or AI models,

00:36:41.000 --> 00:36:42.600
being a pharmacogeneticist

00:36:42.600 --> 00:36:45.080
but not fitting models or doing that kind of stuff.

00:36:45.639 --> 00:36:47.800
And Eric nicely chimed in and said,

00:36:48.919 --> 00:36:50.280
I know you feel your pain

00:36:50.280 --> 00:36:52.360
or something worse to that effect.

00:36:52.360 --> 00:36:55.959
So I guess being a square peg

00:36:56.760 --> 00:36:59.320
in an organization is a tough thing, right?

00:36:59.320 --> 00:37:04.120
Because you are not like the others.

00:37:04.840 --> 00:37:07.560
So what advice would you give

00:37:07.560 --> 00:37:09.479
other similar square pegs

00:37:09.479 --> 00:37:12.040
who may be sitting in other organizations

00:37:12.600 --> 00:37:13.560
and maybe on this call?

00:37:15.000 --> 00:37:16.600
Well, I'm glad you chimed in on this.

00:37:16.600 --> 00:37:17.879
And I remember when you put that post,

00:37:17.879 --> 00:37:20.280
I was like, okay, yeah, I feel seen on this for sure.

00:37:21.239 --> 00:37:22.840
And Mike's a good friend.

00:37:22.840 --> 00:37:24.040
So I'm really glad you're here.

00:37:24.919 --> 00:37:27.560
So I think one thing that's helped me

00:37:28.520 --> 00:37:30.360
as I struggle with this,

00:37:30.360 --> 00:37:31.320
sometimes to this day,

00:37:31.320 --> 00:37:32.600
still struggle with parts of this,

00:37:33.320 --> 00:37:35.800
is not being afraid of it,

00:37:35.800 --> 00:37:37.800
but using the strengths

00:37:37.800 --> 00:37:41.879
to help better the people around me immediately

00:37:41.879 --> 00:37:43.719
and then letting that kind of spread out.

00:37:43.719 --> 00:37:45.560
So I won't lie,

00:37:45.560 --> 00:37:47.239
there's some pressure being known

00:37:47.320 --> 00:37:50.439
as one of the R people at the org

00:37:51.080 --> 00:37:54.520
that people go to for questions every week or whatnot.

00:37:54.520 --> 00:37:56.679
But what I've been trying to do

00:37:56.679 --> 00:37:59.000
is kind of what I said earlier,

00:37:59.000 --> 00:38:01.320
bring up others around me

00:38:01.320 --> 00:38:04.520
to help carry out certain messages

00:38:04.520 --> 00:38:08.280
or certain steps in what makes me that square peg,

00:38:08.280 --> 00:38:10.439
kind of showing where these skills are applied

00:38:10.439 --> 00:38:11.560
in what situation

00:38:11.560 --> 00:38:13.479
and getting some help along the way.

