Thanks for joining.

00:45:25.340 --> 00:45:25.820
Yeah, yeah.

00:45:25.820 --> 00:45:26.939
Thanks for the great question.

00:45:28.459 --> 00:45:30.060
In the industry these days,

00:45:30.860 --> 00:45:33.659
I think some of the best things to help,

00:45:33.659 --> 00:45:35.100
you might say, break in

00:45:35.100 --> 00:45:38.459
is maybe this will go to other industries as well.

00:45:38.459 --> 00:45:40.620
And I'm curious what the people in the chat think of this.

00:45:40.620 --> 00:45:44.219
But even just finding an example data set

00:45:44.219 --> 00:45:47.340
or an example domain that you want to maybe practice

00:45:48.219 --> 00:45:50.860
say analytical skills on and sharing that

00:45:50.860 --> 00:45:54.379
as like a blog or another online resource,

00:45:54.379 --> 00:45:57.100
start building up that portfolio a bit.

00:45:57.100 --> 00:45:59.260
I can tell you that if I see

00:45:59.340 --> 00:46:02.459
like a CV or resume come

00:46:02.459 --> 00:46:05.100
and they asked me to do like an onsite interview

00:46:05.100 --> 00:46:06.300
or a phone interview,

00:46:06.860 --> 00:46:08.459
and I'm going to look at that CV

00:46:08.459 --> 00:46:09.899
and they have a GitHub profile.

00:46:09.899 --> 00:46:11.179
Oh yeah, I'm going to be looking at that

00:46:11.179 --> 00:46:12.860
and I'm going to be very interested

00:46:12.860 --> 00:46:14.540
because it means that they're trying to

00:46:15.260 --> 00:46:17.899
build up their skillset in the open.

00:46:17.899 --> 00:46:19.580
And I'm not going to require everybody to do that

00:46:19.580 --> 00:46:21.899
because me of all people,

00:46:21.899 --> 00:46:24.459
I know how precious time can be,

00:46:24.459 --> 00:46:27.260
especially when you have other personal responsibilities,

00:46:27.260 --> 00:46:29.820
but finding some avenue to put yourself out there

00:46:29.820 --> 00:46:31.260
that will go a long way.

00:46:31.260 --> 00:46:34.459
But I'm sure there are quite a few companies.

00:46:34.459 --> 00:46:37.739
And in fact, my company just posted a couple of positions.

00:46:37.739 --> 00:46:40.300
We're looking for some orange, shiny talent as well.

00:46:42.060 --> 00:46:43.739
There's definitely opportunities out there.

00:46:43.739 --> 00:46:47.260
I think the key is kind of showing that skillset

00:46:47.260 --> 00:46:48.699
that you're building up

00:46:48.699 --> 00:46:52.540
and then being able to really embrace the idea

00:46:52.540 --> 00:46:55.419
of using R, using other languages

00:46:55.419 --> 00:46:58.300
to really do an innovative analysis.

00:46:58.300 --> 00:47:00.780
I agree, it's not easy in the beginning,

00:47:00.780 --> 00:47:02.379
but building out that portfolio,

00:47:02.379 --> 00:47:03.899
I think will be a big help.

